Place squash and carrots in large pot. Add chicken broth and water; stir. Bring to boil over medium-high heat; cover. Reduce heat to medium-low; simmer 10 minutes or until vegetables are tender. Cool slightly. Add chicken broth mixture to food processor or blender container in small batches; cover. Process until pureed. Return to pot; keep warm on low heat. Repeat with remaining chicken broth mixture. Stir in pepper and nutmeg. Remove from heat. Add a few tablespoonfuls of hot soup to sour cream in small bowl; mix well. Return to soup in pot; stir until well blended.